    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-08T17:04:32+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-08T17:04:32+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T07:34:32Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T07:34:32Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A trough will linger inland over the west until a cold front sweeps across southern SA on Thursday. This front will push the inland trough into the far north, exiting the state early Friday. A cooler southwest to southerly flow will gradually moderate in the wake of the front as a strong high pressure system moves in from the west from Friday, establishing in the Bight on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW013" description="North West Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-08T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower south of Woomera, near zero chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm in the far west. Winds northwest to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h tending northwest to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h in the late afternoon.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers south of Coober Pedy, most likely in the morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm south of Coober Pedy in the morning and afternoon. Winds northwest to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h becoming northwesterly 20 to 30 km/h in the morning then tending southeast to southwesterly in the middle of the day. Overnight temperatures falling to between 16 and 23 with daytime temperatures reaching 26 to 37.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:20am to 3:40pm, UV Index predicted to reach 8 [Very High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Winds southeast to southwesterly 25 to 35 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 12 and 18 with daytime temperatures reaching 21 to 27.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-12T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-11T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Winds south to southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 9 and 12 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-04-12T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-13T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-11T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-12T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to around 9 with daytime temperatures reaching 20 to 25.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
